Rating: 4
This is an incredible wonderful soup! Definitely a new favorite for me and my husband. We plan to serve it at Thanksgiving this year. Unlike many of the other reviewers, I stuck to the recipe and simply used water instead of stock. By just adding a little salt and a lot of pepper (to spice it up a bit), the soup tasted great and fatty/salty stocks are not needed. Also, the soup was so creamy and wonderful after I pureed it that the cream definitely wasn't needed. If any of you are thinking of making this soup, please don't skip the sauted shiitakes and brown butter...what an amazing finish to the soup!

Rating: 4
This is a family favourite. I don't use chicken broth, but I don't use plain water, either. I make a stock with the peelings of the celeriac, mushroom stems, a chopped onion. I also sweat the shallots, celeriac & celery, and develop a bit of a fond on the bottom of the pot. I strain the stock through a coffee filter before adding it to the sweated veg. That extra hit of celery stock really intensifies the flavour. I don't use the cream, lemon juice, or lots of salt. Usually use more mushrooms, but that's it.

