Rating: 4
I thought this was terriffic, but I do confess to making some changes. Most important, I used a full, rich, homemade chicken stock, and I reduced the amount to 6 cups for a little thicker product. While I was prepping the vegetables, I pre-seasoned my stock by adding some leek greens, a small carrot,(actually, I scrubbed the carrot and then peeled it, using the peel for my stock and the carrot for something else) the stems from the shitakes, the cores from the celery roots-- chunked, a pinch of nutmeg, and some fennel fronds (not stems). I let it simmer for about 30 minutes before I sieved it for my bisque. I added the celery root, etc. to the stock instead of vice versa so I could use the same butter to saute the mushrooms, thus eliminating the fat from the soup itself. I also used alot more salt. 2 tspns for 1/2 gallon of stock was definitely not enough for our tastes. At the last minute before serving, I sirred in a pinch of fresh, finely chopped mint. Awesome. Next time I'm adding fennel, and possibly shrimp.

